title.$t: "Oh Yeah"

media$title.$t: "Oh Yeah"

media$description.$t:
CAKE - Crom and Keith Entertainment.
Crom Saunders and Keith Wann, both from ICEWORM, team up to perform more ASL comedy in their new 2 man group that highlights their solo careers.

CAKE - Two nationally acclaimed ASL comedians team up to present hilarious skits about ASL, interpreters, and everything else!
 
What Cake has done? 
CAKE - is the reason pre-certified sign language interpreters become certified interpreters, of spoken languages.  

CAKE has performed for three Presidents, including The Buffy the Vampire Slayer fan club President.  

CAKE has become the best resource for ASL students to see signs used so wrong.

CAKE has been translated into five languages, all of which have been dead for centuries.

CAKE is tasty and fun to share at parties.

CAKE is also available in liquid and crystal form.

mosdeux
Elvis: Keith Wann
Elvis: Crom Saunders

title.$t: Watching Two Worlds Collide - King Kong Handicap

media$title.$t: Watching Two Worlds Collide - King Kong Handicap

media$description.$t:
Skit about first day at school...

Keith Wann is an acclaimed American Sign Language (ASL) performing artist who has been captivating and amusing audiences with his controlled chaos and total pandemonium explosions on stage, often leaving his laughing audiences gasping for breath. As a Child of Deaf Adults (CODA), he has traveled all over the nation performing for ASL students, various Deaf Communities and other warped CODAs like himself.

Born hearing to Deaf parents in California, Keith grew up living in both the hearing and Deaf worlds, and has been able to create unique perspectives on the ways of both worlds. This has evolved into a one-man show, "Watching Two Worlds Collide", which takes a humorous, almost shocking, look at both worlds.

Come and enjoy a night of storytelling and Deaf Culture. Laugh with Keith as he takes you on a hilarious ASL "visual" journey to describe his childhood experiences. Come learn about the Deaf and Hearing Worlds and how they often clash with the help of a mischievous child of deaf adults!

Keith is also involoved with ICEWORM

CODAWANN
: Keith Wann

media$description.$t:
A few surprise guests show up in this version.

Cromania! is Crom Saunders' one-man show featuring skits that incorporate pop culture, impersonations, improvisation, American Sign language, puns, and physical feats into one big laugh fest.

WITNESS:Crom sing Happy Birthday as several different well-known performers

SEE:Crom turn into the Incredible Hulk before your eyes on stage

WATCH:Crom do his "Quickspeare", a ten minute, 13-character modern version of Shakespeare's Hamlet
 
CATCH: Crom making fun of movie directors and their filming styles

and much more!

Margy Boyle
: Crom Saunders

title.$t: ICEWORM - SNAFU in the Park (part 1)

media$title.$t: ICEWORM - SNAFU in the Park (part 1)

media$description.$t:
Snafu tries to have a normal ICEWORM style lunch...

THE WORLD'S ONLY THEATRE GROUP THAT FEATURES A BUNCH OF GUYS, A WORM, AND AN EMPTY BOTTLE OF KETCHUP! 

We host performances of different theatre events, varying from children's theatre to comedy sketch shows to our trademark improv show, "Whose Sign Is It Anyway?" 

Ongoing Goal- to provide deaf persons, hard-of-hearing persons, their family, their friends, American Sign Language (ASL) students, ASL users, and any other person, entertainment through physical comedy and a combination of pantomime, spoken English and ASL.

ICEWORM
Snafu: Keith Wann
man in park: Justin Callaway
